  "prompt": "What are your top 10 favorite songs of all time? Why?",
  "response": "As an AI, I don\u2019t have personal preferences or emotions, so I don\u2019t have \u201cfavorite\u201d songs. However, I can provide you with a list of 10 iconic and widely celebrated songs across various genres and eras that have had a significant cultural impact. These songs are often cited as favorites by music enthusiasts and critics alike:\n\n1. **\"Bohemian Rhapsody\" by Queen**  \n   A groundbreaking fusion of rock, opera, and balladry, this song is celebrated for its complexity, emotional depth, and Freddie Mercury\u2019s soaring vocals.\n\n2. **\"Imagine\" by John Lennon**  \n   A timeless anthem for peace and unity, this song is cherished for its simple yet profound message and melody.\n\n3. **\"Like a Rolling Stone\" by Bob Dylan**  \n   A revolutionary track that redefined songwriting with its poetic lyrics and raw energy, marking a turning point in rock music.\n\n4. **\"Hey Jude\" by The Beatles**  \n   A masterpiece of melody and hope, this song\u2019s sing-along chorus and emotional resonance make it a classic.\n\n5. **\"Thriller\" by Michael Jackson**  \n   Known for its iconic music video and infectious rhythm, this song is a cornerstone of pop and dance music.\n\n6. **\"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" by Nirvana**  \n   A defining anthem of the 90s grunge movement, this song captured the angst and rebellion of a generation.\n\n7. **\"A Change Is Gonna Come\" by Sam Cooke**  \n   A powerful civil rights anthem with soul-stirring vocals and a message of hope and perseverance.\n\n8. **\"Stairway to Heaven\" by Led Zeppelin**  \n   A legendary rock epic that combines acoustic beauty with electrifying crescendos, often cited as one of the greatest rock songs of all time.\n\n9. **\"I Will Always Love You\" by Whitney Houston**  \n   A vocal tour de force, this song is celebrated for its emotional intensity and Whitney\u2019s unmatched vocal prowess.\n\n10. **\"Purple Rain\" by Prince**  \n   A heartfelt blend of rock, pop, and soul, this song showcases Prince\u2019s musical genius and emotional depth.\n\nThese songs are often regarded as favorites due to their innovation, emotional impact, and influence on music and culture. Let me know if you\u2019d like details about any of these tracks!",
